==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spur-royal
<hw>Spur"-roy`al</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ucir⟧r"roi`⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A gold coin, first made in the reign of Edward IV., having a star
on the reverse resembling the rowel of a spur. In the reigns of
Elizabeth and of James I., its value was fifteen shillings.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>spur-rial</asp>, and
<asp>spur-ryal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurry</ent>⟦br⟧
